## LO SIN^ YOURSELETO BANALITY

Describing this sensation  is tricky, because the fae won't remember sliding into  Banality.  That's  kind of the  point,  actually.  For those  who  have a little  more time to  witness  their  own  decline, though, the  ride is no  less horrifying. First,  the colors of  the chimerical  world start looking  bleached, the sounds come across flat, the once-charming  scents become tired and musty. Like a receiver picking up two stations at  once,  the mortal  world begins to overlap  the chimerical  more and more often. The overlap  from mere flickering  seconds to  several minutes  at a time,  which  can  have  predictably disastrous  consequences  in  moments  of stress

